cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.HC 

This paper involves learning from human demonstrations and using gaze information to improve performance in visuomotor tasks. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of deep neural networks for prediction suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The focus on improving task performance suggests that it may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the use of human gaze data suggests that it may also belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
